WEBVTT

00:21.021 --> 00:23.982
[Marty] Okay, our partner thinks
that she's a good hire,

00:24.065 --> 00:26.151
-and you weren't at that meeting.
-No, I was at the casino

00:26.234 --> 00:27.193
covering your ass.

00:27.819 --> 00:29.362
Well, I wasn't exactly on vacation.

00:29.446 --> 00:31.698
-No, I know that.
-I was under a great deal of pressure.

00:31.781 --> 00:34.534
Yeah, but you made
a huge unilateral decision.

00:36.119 --> 00:40.165
[Sue] Wendy, did why do you feel
so resistant to hiring,

00:40.248 --> 00:42.167
-um... Maya?
-Maya. Maya. Maya.

00:43.043 --> 00:45.962
This isn't about her resume, is it?

00:46.671 --> 00:48.339
It's personal for you.

00:48.423 --> 00:51.843
No, no, no. No, not at all. I just...

00:53.636 --> 00:57.182
I just think that it is a <i>huge</i> risk

00:57.432 --> 01:01.728
to put somebody with such radically
different viewpoints from ours

01:01.811 --> 01:05.023
in a position of power in our life.
Like, I understand...

01:06.066 --> 01:09.027
I understand you are under
a lot of pressure, and I am...

01:09.736 --> 01:12.238
I'm so sorry you went through that,

01:12.655 --> 01:16.117
but Maya is not the answer
to any of our problems.

01:16.284 --> 01:18.203
Fine. Our partner thinks that she is.

01:18.286 --> 01:19.621
Yeah, well, I disagree.

01:19.746 --> 01:22.415
[Sue] Good. Good communication.

01:23.124 --> 01:26.586
Can you access some feeling words?

01:28.838 --> 01:30.340
I'm scared!

01:31.841 --> 01:34.094
I'm fucking terrified, actually.

01:34.302 --> 01:38.098
-[Sue] Ooh, those are strong feelings.
-Let me tell you why you're scared, Wendy.

01:38.181 --> 01:39.766
You don't believe in your husband.

01:39.849 --> 01:42.644
-Yet, I have kept us safe this entire--
-"Safe"?

01:42.727 --> 01:45.146
For some reason, you think that
you're somehow incapable--

01:45.230 --> 01:47.816
-You think we're safe?
-I do think that we're safe.

01:47.899 --> 01:48.733
[Wendy] Ha!

01:49.651 --> 01:51.694
-Gonna help me out here, Sue?
-Yeah! That'd be great.

01:51.778 --> 01:54.656
Can you explain to her that
everything that I do is for the family?

01:54.739 --> 01:57.867
Oh, and can you explain to him
that <i>that</i> is complete bullshit?

01:58.660 --> 02:02.455
I think that the two of you
are doing a terrific job

02:02.539 --> 02:03.957
at talking this out.

02:04.457 --> 02:07.001
Really? 'Cause I feel like
we're going in circles.

02:07.127 --> 02:10.338
So, please... weigh in.

02:10.421 --> 02:11.673
You gotta have something to say.

02:15.343 --> 02:18.096
I do, actually.

02:20.098 --> 02:23.017
What does it say about a marriage

02:23.434 --> 02:29.190
when a husband and wife
both try to bribe the therapist?

02:32.026 --> 02:34.487
You're both paying me off.

02:35.738 --> 02:38.199
There. I said it.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.332
-What the fuck is wrong with you?
-Fuck's wrong with you?

02:46.416 --> 02:48.168
-You did the same goddamn thing I did.
-Once!

02:48.251 --> 02:49.502
-Once!
-You're a fucking beauty.

02:49.586 --> 02:52.130
Because I was worried when you came back
with that crazy idea,

02:52.255 --> 02:54.883
and I wanted Sue to work a little harder.

02:54.966 --> 02:57.135
You people don't make it easy for anybody.

02:57.218 --> 02:58.553
Just shut the fuck up, Sue.

02:58.636 --> 03:01.014
No, wait.
Have you been doing this the entire time?

03:01.097 --> 03:02.765
Are you that insecure?

03:02.849 --> 03:06.394
No, I'm that ignored, Wendy.
You wanna know why I'm bribing this woman?

03:06.477 --> 03:08.563
It's because you're completely incapable
of listening.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.148
This is my only chance
to convince you

03:10.231 --> 03:12.483
that what you are doing
is putting us in danger.

03:12.567 --> 03:14.360
First, you force us to stay here.

03:14.444 --> 03:17.030
Second, you dig us in so deep,
we're never going to get out.

03:17.155 --> 03:19.657
And now I discover that you've been
pouring your heart out

03:19.741 --> 03:22.118
on the phone every night to Navarro,

03:22.202 --> 03:24.579
interpreting his fucking omens.

03:24.954 --> 03:26.372
What is wrong with you?

03:26.456 --> 03:28.666
-You get how dangerous that is?
-You're listening to my calls.

03:28.750 --> 03:30.418
Wanna know what happened
to the maid that lost the teeth?

03:30.501 --> 03:31.711
-You're jealous.
-He killed her.

03:31.794 --> 03:34.380
You're jealous, that's what this is about.
You can't keep up with me.

03:34.464 --> 03:38.134
-Give me a fucking break.
-No, you can't. You can't keep up with me.

03:38.218 --> 03:41.846
And I have one sliver of success,
and you, you lose your mind.

03:41.930 --> 03:44.057
"Success." Chopping the balls off a horse.
Is that success?

03:44.140 --> 03:45.642
-Come on! I didn't know.
-[Marty] Exactly.

03:45.725 --> 03:47.477
Your ambition makes you reckless.

03:47.560 --> 03:49.938
You go into business with a drug lord,

03:50.021 --> 03:51.856
what did you think was gonna happen?

03:51.940 --> 03:53.524
-My ambition?
-Yeah.

03:53.608 --> 03:56.444
You're so arrogant,
you think you can flip an FBI agent.

03:56.527 --> 03:58.571
Do you know how crazy that sounds?

03:58.655 --> 04:00.406
Is it crazier than killing someone?

04:02.325 --> 04:03.493
Don't you dare.

04:04.494 --> 04:06.246
Don't you-- I didn't kill Cade.

04:06.329 --> 04:08.289
No, you had somebody else do it for you.

04:09.540 --> 04:10.416
For our family.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.626
And I stayed with you.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.670
Oh, wow!

04:13.753 --> 04:16.923
Well, does that make you
a big fucking hero?

04:17.465 --> 04:20.802
I only did what I did because you didn't
have the balls to do it yourself.

04:20.885 --> 04:22.929
No, I was busy trying
to get us the fuck out.

04:23.012 --> 04:24.555
-They would've found us.
-No, they wouldn't.

04:24.639 --> 04:26.683
We'd be dead by now if you'd got your way.

04:26.766 --> 04:29.435
You'd say anything
to justify what you did.

04:29.852 --> 04:31.562
I don't know how you live with yourself.

04:33.815 --> 04:35.108
You're an ungrateful prick.

04:35.191 --> 04:38.194
You did exactly what you wanted to do,
and you always have, haven't you?

04:38.278 --> 04:39.112
That is not true.

04:39.195 --> 04:42.240
Gary, Navarro, another casino,
a horse farm.

04:42.323 --> 04:44.367
You put everything before the family.

04:44.450 --> 04:45.368
I am trying.

04:45.451 --> 04:48.997
I am trying to build a future
for our family

04:49.080 --> 04:51.582
out of the mess that you created.

04:51.666 --> 04:55.420
[stammers] And you're too narrow-minded
and jealous to see it.

04:55.503 --> 04:57.714
Right, yeah,
and you're just a fucking scary,

04:57.797 --> 05:00.675
selfish, power-hungry fucking bitch.

05:06.472 --> 05:09.183
Great. Get the fuck out. Do it.

05:09.267 --> 05:11.269
-I don't need you.
-[door opens]

05:11.352 --> 05:14.022
-I don't even fucking know you anymore.
-[door shuts]

05:18.026 --> 05:19.110
[sighs]

05:26.826 --> 05:28.828
[theme music playing]

05:35.626 --> 05:38.671
[Marty] Obviously, we need to discuss
doctor-patient confidentiality.

05:41.674 --> 05:43.259
I mean, I don't have to tell you.

05:43.343 --> 05:46.262
Breathe even a word of this to someone,
it's got some...

05:47.055 --> 05:49.557
pretty nasty implications for your career.

05:50.016 --> 05:52.602
And for you and Wendy, I imagine.

05:54.187 --> 05:55.521
[Marty] Hmm.

05:58.024 --> 05:59.525
How much money do you want?

06:00.443 --> 06:02.278
It's not about money, Marty.

06:02.487 --> 06:03.446
How much?

06:07.825 --> 06:09.202
A shitload.

06:09.327 --> 06:11.329
Mm-hmm. Yeah, that's what I thought.

06:23.633 --> 06:24.926
Get in the car, Wendy.

06:30.348 --> 06:31.516
You're gonna walk home?

06:32.517 --> 06:36.104
Home is a 43-minute walk from here.

06:36.604 --> 06:38.940
By the time I get there, I want you out.

06:53.663 --> 06:54.580
[Sam] Thanks.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.334
What's with all the federal agents?

06:58.418 --> 07:01.254
All good, Sam. Casinos are regulated.

07:01.337 --> 07:02.505
Regulated how?

07:02.797 --> 07:04.549
Just... regulated.

07:05.341 --> 07:06.676
What are they regulating?

07:06.759 --> 07:09.804
[sighs]
They're called compliance officers.

07:10.596 --> 07:11.472
All normal.

07:11.556 --> 07:13.850
Just don't look like
you're trying to lose.

07:13.975 --> 07:15.685
Look like you're having fun.

07:18.604 --> 07:21.482
-[Sam sighs]
-Fuckin' smile.

07:26.154 --> 07:28.364
[gamblers cheering]

07:28.448 --> 07:30.074
Hey, you know what this is?

07:31.033 --> 07:33.077
I could not care less what it is.

07:33.286 --> 07:36.456
It's a bill from my body shop for $7,800!

07:36.622 --> 07:37.874
For bird shit?

07:38.875 --> 07:41.085
For a custom paint job on my Trans Am.

07:41.169 --> 07:42.545
A little steep, don't you think?

07:42.628 --> 07:45.047
Considering the car is not worth
hardly half of that.

07:45.131 --> 07:47.133
Well, that's what it's gonna cost you.

07:47.300 --> 07:50.136
You and me are even.

07:50.219 --> 07:52.472
Call the Audubon Society or some shit.

07:52.555 --> 07:55.099
Better yet, the casino gives loans now.

07:55.183 --> 07:57.059
I can get you an application.

07:57.727 --> 08:00.813
Hey, this whole anti-authority thing
you got going on,

08:00.938 --> 08:02.440
it's gonna get you hurt.

08:07.028 --> 08:08.696
You're fucking touching me.

08:18.331 --> 08:21.250
I'm making some changes
with tomorrow's drop.

08:21.334 --> 08:22.877
I already talked to my boys.

08:22.960 --> 08:25.254
The abandoned stadium
off of Woodrow Wilson.

08:25.379 --> 08:26.672
-It's quiet.
-No.

08:27.006 --> 08:29.050
The drive-in in Branch. Got it?

08:29.175 --> 08:31.969
What the fuck is your problem?
That stadium is a good drop.

08:32.053 --> 08:33.638
No, the last time you picked,

08:33.721 --> 08:35.306
your crew tried to fuck with me

08:35.389 --> 08:38.226
and jeopardized a shit-ton of money, so...

08:43.564 --> 08:45.650
And you ain't a fucking authority!

09:03.918 --> 09:05.253
You heard from Omar?

09:06.337 --> 09:08.381
If you're wondering
if he's still angry with you,

09:08.464 --> 09:09.966
yes, he's still angry.

09:10.091 --> 09:12.260
Next time I give you advice, listen to it.

09:15.304 --> 09:17.723
-Mmm.
-I know. We need a new machine.

09:21.727 --> 09:25.064
I should probably let you know,
Marty and I are taking some time apart.

09:29.652 --> 09:30.570
Why?

09:33.155 --> 09:34.365
We had a fight.

09:35.157 --> 09:36.784
-What kind of a fight?
-A big one.

09:37.451 --> 09:39.078
You're not splitting up, I hope.

09:39.495 --> 09:41.497
No. No, I don't know.

09:43.332 --> 09:45.835
He was being a dick, so I tossed him out.

09:46.752 --> 09:47.795
You know how it goes.

09:49.130 --> 09:50.089
I do.

09:51.048 --> 09:54.302
I also know to never underestimate
the power of somebody moving out,

09:54.427 --> 09:55.511
however briefly.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.430
Well, we're still business partners.

09:57.513 --> 10:00.308
Everything will function exactly
as it has before.

10:00.391 --> 10:02.351
I just don't have to deal with his shit
right now.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.604
You say that, but the first time you--
[sighs]

10:04.687 --> 10:06.355
Jesus Christ. The fuck is she doing here?

10:11.444 --> 10:13.487
I want to talk to your boss, alone.

10:14.989 --> 10:16.032
Where's Zeke?

10:16.616 --> 10:18.326
-With my lover.
-Oh, right.

10:18.826 --> 10:20.119
It's summer vacation.

10:21.037 --> 10:22.204
Don't you worry about Zeke.

10:22.288 --> 10:25.499
He is safe and sound
and none of your business.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.209
Judge told you that.

10:29.754 --> 10:31.130
What do you want, Darlene?

10:31.547 --> 10:34.967
I've re-planted my crop.
We're back in business.

10:35.176 --> 10:37.094
I came about our distribution deal.

10:37.219 --> 10:38.888
Are you out of your mind?

10:38.971 --> 10:41.724
You can't plant poppies
that close to the casino.

10:42.224 --> 10:43.643
This is my land.

10:43.976 --> 10:45.936
We'll be up and running in four months.

10:46.020 --> 10:48.689
You killed 57 people

10:48.773 --> 10:50.358
when you spiked our dope.

10:50.441 --> 10:51.651
Junkies.

10:52.318 --> 10:54.987
That is dirty water under an old bridge.

10:55.071 --> 10:58.282
I don't care. Your deal went away
the second that you crossed the cartel.

11:00.451 --> 11:01.952
[Darlene] You burned our fields.

11:02.328 --> 11:05.623
You took our land
for this monstrosity of a casino.

11:05.706 --> 11:06.916
Whose profits you enjoy.

11:07.041 --> 11:09.043
And now you're going back on your word?

11:09.126 --> 11:11.837
You made a commitment. You owe us.

11:11.921 --> 11:14.840
The last thing that we promised you
was to spare your life.

11:14.924 --> 11:17.885
Don't make us go back on that one.
Now get the fuck out of my office.

11:18.636 --> 11:21.263
Broken promises got consequences.

11:21.764 --> 11:22.848
Bring 'em on.

11:41.826 --> 11:44.203
[Marty] <i>You had a guy killed, Wendy.</i>

11:44.286 --> 11:46.372
Does that weigh on your conscience at all?

11:46.455 --> 11:47.707
'Cause I don't see it.

11:47.790 --> 11:51.335
And now I'm-- I'm weak,
because I've got a soul.

11:51.419 --> 11:52.461
That's rich.

11:52.545 --> 11:53.879
You're so...

11:53.963 --> 11:57.967
so calm, so cold after Mason's death.

11:58.050 --> 11:59.885
Like it never fucking happened.

11:59.969 --> 12:01.220
Well, we could have gotten out.

12:01.303 --> 12:03.514
It all would have worked,
but you didn't want that.

12:03.597 --> 12:05.599
I saved us,
you pulled us right back into the shit.

12:05.683 --> 12:07.059
Now I gotta save us all over again.

12:07.143 --> 12:10.104
And I'm fucking arrogant?
Are you fucking kidding me?

12:10.187 --> 12:12.273
I'm doing exactly what you wanted.

12:12.356 --> 12:14.108
You wanted me to step up,
I'm stepping up,

12:14.233 --> 12:16.777
and you cannot even back
that one goddamn play.

12:16.861 --> 12:20.239
You think I'm gonna apologize
for protecting my family?

12:20.322 --> 12:21.449
You're out of your mind.

12:22.032 --> 12:24.493
You're out of your fucking mind.

12:40.718 --> 12:41.594
Hi.

12:42.011 --> 12:44.096
Hey. How are you doing?

12:44.722 --> 12:48.350
Uh, not great, actually.
Wendy and I had a fight, if you must know.

12:48.726 --> 12:50.394
Sorry, that sucks.

12:50.686 --> 12:52.855
Yeah, I was thinking that, um,

12:52.938 --> 12:56.650
I might go check out that place
that they put you up in. Do you like it?

12:57.067 --> 12:58.527
Yeah, it's great.

12:58.694 --> 13:00.780
As long as you don't care
about aesthetics.

13:00.863 --> 13:03.657
Or comfort or hygiene.

13:04.617 --> 13:06.452
Uh, it's got a roof though, right?

13:08.037 --> 13:08.913
[Maya] Hmm.

13:14.585 --> 13:16.170
-What's this?
-It's a confession.

13:17.046 --> 13:18.339
All you gotta do is sign.

13:18.422 --> 13:22.134
Oh, yeah. I gotta--
I gotta check with Wendy first. Okay?

13:22.927 --> 13:24.595
[Maya] Is this what you're fighting over?

13:25.429 --> 13:28.390
It is part of it, uh, you know.
She'll get there.

13:28.474 --> 13:31.519
-I just need a little bit of time.
-You know what this looks like, right?

13:31.602 --> 13:35.064
It looks like I'm stalling, but I'm not.
I just moved out of the house, so...

13:36.774 --> 13:39.318
Look, I went out on a limb
to get you this deal.

13:39.735 --> 13:42.613
Just look at it.
Cross out anything you don't like.

13:42.696 --> 13:44.865
[stammers] Can I be honest with you?

13:44.949 --> 13:46.116
I don't know yet.

13:46.742 --> 13:49.203
Uh, I don't-- I don't trust you.

13:50.246 --> 13:51.121
Okay.

13:51.330 --> 13:54.542
You know, there's a big risk for me,
and you can dress it up as safe,

13:54.625 --> 13:56.544
but we both know it's not that simple.

13:56.794 --> 14:00.089
-And everything I know about the FBI--
-You haven't had good agents on your case.

14:00.422 --> 14:02.633
Well, are there any? You know, I mean...

14:03.968 --> 14:06.011
Evans is out for blood, and...

14:07.221 --> 14:08.514
Petty was a sociopath.

14:08.597 --> 14:11.475
You know, he, um,
he got one of my people hooked on drugs.

14:11.559 --> 14:14.770
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry.
Look, I will deny ever saying it.

14:15.271 --> 14:17.898
Agent Petty, dick. Agent Evans, dick.

14:18.315 --> 14:19.525
Shouldn't even be on your case.

14:19.650 --> 14:22.027
Especially not when
the two of them were sleeping together.

14:22.111 --> 14:23.737
Completely unprofessional.

14:24.363 --> 14:26.115
But I'm not them.

14:27.324 --> 14:28.993
But how do I know that? You know?

14:29.326 --> 14:30.369
I don't know that.

14:31.078 --> 14:33.289
You know, this is--
this is a two-way street,

14:33.372 --> 14:35.791
and I tried to prove to you that

14:36.125 --> 14:37.793
I want to do the right thing,

14:37.877 --> 14:39.879
that you can trust me,
and you turned me down.

14:39.962 --> 14:43.257
And so now you gotta prove to me
that I can trust you,

14:43.340 --> 14:45.467
and until I do,
and until Wendy's on board,

14:45.551 --> 14:48.095
I cannot sign anything. I'm sorry.

14:48.178 --> 14:52.600
You know, I mean, I want to work with you,
but not at any cost, so...

15:01.317 --> 15:04.361
[Darlene] <i>You ever notice people</i>
<i>don't honor their word anymore?</i>

15:04.445 --> 15:07.740
Well, I've done everything I can do
for you and baby Zeke, Darlene.

15:08.032 --> 15:09.491
Not talking about you.

15:10.034 --> 15:14.371
The cartel's breaking their agreement
to distribute my product.

15:14.455 --> 15:16.749
Can you believe that? The nerve.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.710
Well, I don't know
what I can do about that.

15:19.793 --> 15:22.129
I can't arrest people
for not doing crime.

15:23.631 --> 15:25.925
How many people you got working under you?

15:26.634 --> 15:28.344
Ten. Count the reserves.

15:29.845 --> 15:31.305
How many you trust?

15:31.931 --> 15:34.767
Your kind of business? Three, four.

15:36.268 --> 15:38.020
That'll do, for a start.

15:38.395 --> 15:39.688
We can always recruit.

15:40.022 --> 15:41.899
People around here trust the police.

15:43.525 --> 15:45.945
[sighs] Darlene, no.

15:46.403 --> 15:48.614
No, come on.
There's limits to what I can do.

15:48.697 --> 15:50.741
Who sets those limits? Not you.

15:50.824 --> 15:54.453
[sighs]
Darlene, I cannot be slinging dope.

15:54.536 --> 15:55.704
Are you kidding me?

15:56.330 --> 15:58.165
How am I even supposed to ask 'em?

15:58.332 --> 16:00.668
You can stand there and refuse me

16:01.168 --> 16:02.920
after all I've done for you?

16:03.420 --> 16:05.589
Jacob's still warm in his grave,

16:05.673 --> 16:08.217
-and you want to cross me now?
-No.

16:14.515 --> 16:16.016
I'm gonna need some time.

16:17.643 --> 16:19.103
Get 'em primed.

16:19.269 --> 16:20.354
Figure it out.

16:20.854 --> 16:22.022
You got three months.

16:23.107 --> 16:26.318
And whatever arrangements you have
with the Byrde family...

16:27.152 --> 16:28.445
that's over.

16:29.029 --> 16:30.823
No more protecting them.

16:31.073 --> 16:33.075
-You got me?
-[door opens]

16:34.034 --> 16:35.035
[door closes]

16:37.246 --> 16:38.080
[sighs]

16:53.637 --> 16:55.764
I thought I told you
to stay away from Erin.

16:55.848 --> 16:57.641
Hmm. She called me.

16:58.767 --> 17:00.394
Well, then don't pick up.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.442
This is a bad idea.

17:06.525 --> 17:10.195
Uh, A of all, he brought us beer.
B of all, it's summer,

17:10.279 --> 17:12.406
and C of all, you're not my mom.

17:14.033 --> 17:15.576
He's not a nice guy, Erin.

17:15.659 --> 17:16.785
